3.1.3 Labels
All platforms, apps, and websites require logical and user-friendly labels that can be accessed by all users and provide adequate context for their location within a page.

3.1.3-A
Elements with the same functionality must be identified consistently.

3.1.3-B
All content must have descriptive and informative page titles.

3.1.3-C
Section headings must be used to organize page content and offer reasonable summaries of the content or actions within the section.

3.1.3-D
Content that needs user input must have labels and instructions to communicate the purpose of the input fields.

3.1.3-E
The purpose of a link must be understandable from the link text.
